delete_metric_run(25.10)                              delete_metric_run(25.10)

Name
       delete_metric_run - Deletes the specified metric run

Syntax
       delete_metric_run

       -help

       [-name <metric_name>]

       Deletes the specified metric run.

       It deletes a set of metrics loaded using read_metric.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each delete_metric_run parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man delete_metric_run

       -name <metric_name>
              Name of the metric run to be deleted. It defaults to  the  "cur-
              rent" run.

              This parameter corresponds to the -id parameter of the read_met-
              ric command.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command deletes run1, which is read by read_met-
                ric.

                read_metric -id run1 metrics.json

                delete_metric_run -name run1

Related Information
              * read_metric

